ENTRY       EC 3.4.24.13                Enzyme
NAME        IgA-specific metalloendopeptidase;
            immunoglobulin A1 proteinase;
            IgA protease;
            IgA1-specific proteinase;
            IgA1 protease;
            IgA1 proteinase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Metalloendopeptidases
REACTION    Cleavage of Pro!Thr bond in the hinge region of the heavy chain of human IgA
COMMENT     A 190 kDa enzyme found in several pathogenic species of Streptococcus such as sanguis and pneumoniae. Type example of peptidase family M26. There is also an IgA-specific prolyl endopeptidase of the serine-type (see EC 3.4.21.72, IgA-specific serine endopeptidase)
